=== Proof of the height theorem ===
Krull’s height theorem can be proved as a consequence of the principal ideal theorem by induction on the number of elements. Let formula_46 be elements in formula_1, formula_2 a minimal prime over formula_49 and formula_6 a prime ideal such that there is no prime strictly between them. Replacing formula_1 by the localization formula_52 we can assume formula_53 is a local ring; note we then have formula_54. By minimality of formula_2, it follows that formula_8 cannot contain all the formula_57; relabeling the subscripts, say, formula_58. Since every prime ideal containing formula_59 is between formula_8 and formula_2, formula_62 and thus we can write for each formula_63,
